# Ken code ownership = REVIEW routing only. CODEOWNERS requests reviews; it does
# not restrict who may edit a path (cross-cutting edits are allowed and simply
# pull the owning area's review). Write/merge restriction is done in branch
# protection, not here.
#
# Model (see docs/ops/github-setup.md and 05-git-and-integration.md):
#   - The Architect is the required reviewer on EVERY PR (the catch-all owner).
#   - The Spec enclave reviews only its own paths (behavioral contract); the
#     conformance CI is Spec's automated gate on every PR.
#   - Owning-team review is NOT a GitHub gate to start — domain correctness is
#     gated pre-PR by each team's QA in the ring.
#   - The Integrator is NOT a reviewer; it is the sole merger, enforced by a
#     branch-protection merge restriction to the `integration` identity.
#
# Authors are typically the `ken-ci` App (not a code owner → no self-approval
# conflict). Reviewer/merger handles must be GitHub teams with member accounts.
# PLACEHOLDER handles — create under the ken-topos org (docs/ops/github-setup.md).

# Architect: required review everywhere.
*                        @ken-topos/architect

# Spec enclave (clean-room): its contract, plus Architect.
/spec/                   @ken-topos/team-spec  @ken-topos/architect
/conformance/            @ken-topos/team-spec  @ken-topos/architect

# --- Optional, enable by uncommenting when the accounts exist ---
# Force Spec (soundness) review on the trusted kernel / prover:
# /crates/ken-kernel/    @ken-topos/team-spec  @ken-topos/architect
# /crates/ken-prover/    @ken-topos/team-spec  @ken-topos/architect
# Steward owns the workflow corpus (Architect co-owns so Steward PRs aren't
# self-approval-blocked):
# /agent/                @ken-topos/steward    @ken-topos/architect
# Librarian owns product docs:
# /docs/                 @ken-topos/librarian  @ken-topos/architect
